05/05/2010
CORFU, Greece -- A court in Corfu on Tuesday (May 4th) sentenced four people to prison for their roles in the fatal carbon monoxide poisoning of two British children at a luxury hotel in 2006.
The hotel manager, a senior maintenance official and the hotel electrician were sentenced to seven years in prison each for negligent manslaughter and causing injury by negligence.
All can appeal their sentences.
A fourth suspect got a two-year suspended sentence for building violations.
Seven other defendants were acquitted.
(AP, BBC - 04/05/10)
